From Ralph Durtschi Subject Re IIsi clock upgrade Hi I have been getting a lot of requests for this information so I thought I would post it for those interested Sorry for length To increase the MacIISi speed to or the clock must be changed from to or This is done by going to a static free work station or putting some aluminum foil down to work Open up the Si by lifting the tabs at the back of the Remove the Hard Disk by disconnecting the power and SCSI cables spreading the tabs and lifting the drive Remove the flopy Remove the power supply by spreading the tab in front and lifting the supply straight up and Remove the fan by pressing the ears together at the back bottom side of the fan and lifting straight up and Remove the Mother Board by spreading the tabs on the left and right side of the board and sliding the board forward then lifting the board all connectors on the back of the board must be removed first Desolder the clock the one closest to the memory modules This is not easy even for a skilled Get an IC socket with the round pins and remove four of the pins by pushing them up from the bottom with long nose Put the four pins in the holes vacated by the clock and solder them a or large power transistor heat sink's on the processor chip and the other large chip just to the right of the processor and figure some way to hold the heat sync's in I made a simple clamp by putting a four inch screw up through the hole in the board between the two Mount the screw using insulated Screw a cross member down over the heat sync's to hold them in Don't use too much Put it all back together and go for Disclaimer this is only the procedure I used and is not authorized by You are on your own for this I'm quite sure it will void your Bye for now Ralph Durtschi Idaho State University EMAIL